comments.content: "female impersonator of New York, today was awarded $240 damages by a jury in the Civil Court of Record after hearing his suit for $1,500 damages from Albert Bouche of Chicago, proprietor of a night club at Miami Beach. The suit alleged breach of verbal contract. Mangum asserted Bouche hired him in New York but discharged him several weeks later. Bouche declared there was no agreement."
